ixture note the voyage was generated 1:1, St. Rose to Thames, but charterers added 4 additional ports (Immingham, Amsterdam, Thames and Huelva) which were charged according to the interim port clause. All time from departure first call Thames through free of cargo in Huelva charged at the $46k demurrage rate. Including bunkers our interim claim totaled $1.06m USD, of which $150k was due consuming 135 MT LSMGO in ECA. Further due vessel\u0027s 2 week stay awaiting berth at St. Rose we sent a $116k demurrage invoice. Otherwise this one turned out to be the most straight forward Marquis voyage operationally, ie no blending or backloading discussions and no last minute attempts to accommodate their receivers."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-03-23T20:09:53.947","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Port costs a bit higher at NOLA partly due to chems, delivery, and terminal fee. Believe pilotage may not have been included in the original generation as well."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-03-16T21:08:31.993","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Thames #1 updated, dems updated"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-03-13T13:35:34.87","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"port costs corrected to reflect interim port, laden passage 1.5 days longer for wx and bunkers up $50k for same reason"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-02-28T14:10:41.46","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"bunker hedge profit estimated"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-02-27T21:45:27.607","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Interim port estimates updated: Bunkers, days, and sailing time"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-02-21T21:00:20.913","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"NOLA departure and 1 day of demurrage"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-01-30T17:41:42.197","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Vessel drifting off ECA to use scrubber. Added a leg to show days at this position."}],"offhireList":[{"id":193758,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":14